  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\nInvestigation is needed as this issue can't be reproduced via same steps/build/device but is critical.\r\nSimilar issue is in status-go: https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/263\r\n\r\n1 send transaction resulted in 2 transactions. So, you sign 1 transfer of 10 ETH and then app makes 2 transfers, of 20 ETH in total.  It was possible to reproduce when:\r\n- recipient username contains ^, e.g. \"^name\"\r\n- sender taps 2 or more times on Confirm button on Unsigned transactions screen after typing a password \r\n\r\nIssue happened at least 13 times but then it stopped occurring. Iâ€™m no longer sure that ^ in the username matters. Here you can see one of the address and pairs of transactions having same sum and very close timestamps: https://ropsten.etherscan.io/txs?a=0xc0112a5e777b4634c7e8256ae3a0b98a70aa0346 \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1 transaction is confirmed, so 1 transaction should be sent. \r\nIf search on ropsten by address of the sender/recipient then only 1 new transaction is shown\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n1 transaction is confirmed but if search on ropsten by address of the sender/recipient then 2 new transaction with same amount are shown\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nhttps://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/6382436/sessions/12/?accessToken=G8Hc9u4VbTBHUyB65BuY3juHT2I on 00:55 - 1:50\r\nRecipient name should contain ^. For example, ^name\r\n- Open Status as sender and sign in\r\n- Open 1-1 chat with ^name\r\n- select send command, username and some sum, e.g. `/send ^name 0.000123` and send it\r\n- on Unsigned transaction screen make sure that only 1 transaction is shown \r\n- type password\r\n- Quickly tap on Confirm button several times (the more the better)\r\n- open https://ropsten.etherscan.io/ and search by address of a sender. Check for new transaction that will be shown in 1-2 minutes. Check that there is only 1 new transaction shown.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: released 0.9.10 and develop build of 0.9.9d139 and PR `account refactoring`https://status-im.slack.com/archives/G53FWGDCM/p1503070357000463\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S6, Android 6.0.1\r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.3.3",
